    <etym xml:lang="ru">Конечное -%ion%i — суффикс. %iBonværn%i = %ibony%i %ifarn%i ‘%sfarn%s дня’;
        %iBonværnon%i— „звезда — вестница дневного %sфарна%s“; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>денница</w><gloss><q>утренняя звезда</q></gloss></mentioned> (от
            <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>день</w></mentioned>). См. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bon"/> ‘день’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_farn"/>. Восстанавливаемое
        *%iBonfarn%i представляет хорошую параллель к <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"
                ><lang/><w>Mihrfarn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><lang/><w>myrprn</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._Sogd."
                /><biblScope>6</biblScope></bibl>), где <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><lang/><w>mihr</w><gloss><q>солнце</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><w/><gloss><q>день</q></gloss></mentioned>, соответствует ос. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_bon"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>164,
                211</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The final -%ion%i is a suffix. %iBonværn%i = %ibony%i %ifarn%i ‘day's
        %sfarn%s’; %iBonværnon%i— „star is day's %sfarn%s messenger“; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>dennitsa</w><gloss><q>morning star</q></gloss></mentioned> (from
            <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>den'</w></mentioned>). See <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bon"/> ‘day’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_farn"/>. The reconstructed
        *%iBonfarn%i represents a good parallel with the <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"
                ><lang/><w>Mihrfarn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><lang/><w>myrprn</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._Sogd."
                /><biblScope>6</biblScope></bibl>), where <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>mihr</w><gloss><q>sun</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>day</q></gloss></mentioned>, corresponds the Ossetic <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_bon"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>164,
                211</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
